f=Governance/sentinel/operational/agent/sentinel-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration sentinel. Gate criteria document paths **board's fields** (board-config.md) sentinel reads them there; sentinel's operational values live here. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Shared with board (single source of truth: board-config.md) --- \· # constitution_path, locked_commitments_path, spend_approval_gate, \· # decision_log_destination  → read from board-config; never duplicated here. \·  \· # --- Sweeps (constitution-watch) ---` · in=Board's fields never set forked constitution path gate value make sentinel watch different rulebook board enforces. Until cadences set, sweeps/scans run operator invokes them, report states monitoring on-demand, continuous gap itself reported. Until scopes set, sentinel samples what operator hands over per-run flags partial coverage. Until contacts set, everything routes operator directly. · f=Unfilled config never silently disables sentinel degrades on-demand, partial, operator-routed monitoring, says report.